INSTALL

    To compile:

	make

    To run:

	make test

    To create documentation in the doc/ subdirectory:

	make doc
    

FILES

    Makefile
	Project Makefile

	The Makefiles are the beginning and the end of this project.  They
	provide most of the framework, as well as documentation.  Read them.

    README
	This file

    Test.java
	Implements the tests, provides the main() entry point, so that the
	project can be run as a stand-alone program

    *.java
	Source code

    test-output
	If tests run correctly, this is the output we expect (used by
	Makefile's test target)

    doc/
	The documentation subdirectory.  The documentation is generated from
	the source code using Javadoc (and possibly other methods)

